# Octavia - Root Environment Configuration
# This file serves as a template for environment variables
# Copy backend .env.example to octavia-backend/.env
# Copy frontend .env.example to octavia-web/.env.local

# ====== BACKEND SETUP ======
# Location: octavia-backend/.env
# Copy octavia-backend/.env.example to .env and configure:
# - DATABASE_URL (use SQLite for dev, PostgreSQL for prod)
# - SECRET_KEY (generate with: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))")
# - OPENAI_API_KEY (for Whisper transcription)
# - POLAR_API_KEY (for payment processing)
# - CELERY_BROKER_URL (for task queue)

# ====== FRONTEND SETUP ======
# Location: octavia-web/.env.local
# Copy octavia-web/.env.example to .env.local and configure:
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL (should match your backend URL)
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_POLAR_API_KEY (public key, safe to expose)

# ====== LOCAL DEVELOPMENT ======
# 1. cd octavia-backend
#    cp .env.example .env
#    # Edit .env with your API keys
#
# 2. cd ../octavia-web
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#    # Edit .env.local if needed
#
# 3. cd ..
#    python run_server.py    # Terminal 1 - Backend
#    npm run dev             # Terminal 2 - Frontend (in octavia-web)

# ====== PRODUCTION SETUP ======
# 1. Use environment variables provided by hosting platform
# 2. Set DEBUG=False in backend
# 3. Use PostgreSQL instead of SQLite
# 4. Configure HTTPS (CORS, SSL certificates)
# 5. Set proper SECRET_KEY (use strong random value)
# 6. Configure real email/SMTP service
# 7. Use production Polar.sh credentials

# ====== NEVER COMMIT ======
# - .env (anywhere)
# - .env.local
# - .env.production
# - Any file with actual API keys, passwords, or secrets
# - Only commit .env.example files as templates
